September 8 at 3:00 PM ¬∑

This Tuesday‚Äôs Class ‚ÄòB‚Äôeats Spotlight is Hillsboro-Central Valley volleyball player, Sydni Culp!

Q: What position do you play, and do you enjoy it?
A: Middle hitter, and yes I enjoy it very much!

Q: Who is your volleyball inspiration? What do you admire most about that person?
A: Saige Forseth because she‚Äôs encouraged me when I was the youngest on the court.

Q: What is your favorite memory with your team?
A: Wednesday optional practices in junior high were the best times of my life.

Q: What is your favorite post-game meal or snack?
A: Literally anything that‚Äôs put in front of me

Q: What is one fun fact about you that few people would know?
A: I‚Äôm the same height as my dad and I‚Äôm taller than 3/4 of my family.

Feel free to share this post, so Sydni and other Class B athletes receive the recognition they deserve!

shared_text:
Hillsboro Dollars for Scholars
May 27 at 11:41 AM ¬∑

The Hillsboro class of 2020 received over $106,000 in scholarships on Sunday! Amazing!
Seniors/parents: Each student received a packet at the graduation ceremony. These contain thank you notes and a college intentions blue slip.
It is VERY important that students get those thank you notes in the mail in the next week. Please take time to let our donors know a little bit about you and what your college plans are.
The college intentions blue slip needs to be mailed in the enclosed envelope or dropped at the high school so that we know where to direct your check in the fall.
If you have any questions about anything related to H509 please contact a board member.
Congratulations! Great things to come for this amazing class.

post_text: The school will push out information about the Hillsboro Fitness Center re-opening with guidelines this week.
shared_text:
Hillsboro Banner
May 26 at 11:48 AM ¬∑

The Hillsboro Fitness Center will reopen at 5 a.m. Monday, June 1. Hillsboro Public Schools Superintendent Paula Suda said Tuesday that the facility's doors and restrooms will be cleaned three times a day and clients are asked to wipe down their equipment before and after use. Masks will not be required. Previously purchased memberships will be extended and those who are not comfortable returning to the center will have their memberships put on hold. More details in Friday's Banner.

post_text: A fun league for young Burros!
shared_text:
SITES.GOOGLE.COM
HCV Athletics

Central Valley Public School
January 6 at 11:33 AM ¬∑

Grand Forks Youth Basketball League

The Grand Forks YMCA is taking registrations until January 13th for students in grades 2-6 who want to play in their Youth Basketball League (YBL).

The season goes from Jan 14th - March 5th. Practices are Tuesday/Thursday from 5:30-6:30 with Games on Saturdays. They try to keep students from the same schools on teams (HCV).

Visit the HCV website or http://www.gfymca.org/category/events/#more-8921 for more information and the registration form.

There are some Central Valley 2nd Grade boys already signed up to play - We would like more students from HCV to participate!

https://sites.google.com/site/hcvathletics/
